DIARRHEA - NIGERIA: (ZAMFARA) FATAL, COMMENT, POSSIBLE ERGOT POISONING
**********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 18 Mar 2016
From: Steve Berger <steve@gideononline.com> [edited]


Regarding: Diarrhea, fatal - Nigeria (Zamfara State) in Cholera, diarrhea & dysentery update (10): Africa, Americas 20160318.4102278, an outbreak of foodborne illness characterized by diarrhea, ascending "leg discoloration" and high mortality rate is suggestive of ergot poisoning.

--
Steve Berger MD
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
Tel Aviv
Israel
<steve@gideononline.com>

[ProMED-mail thanks Dr. Steve Berger for his comment. While the symptoms of ergot poisoning (http://digitalhistorysalem.weebly.com/ergot-poisoning.html) include crawling sensations in the skin, tingling in the fingers, vertigo, tinnitus, headaches, disturbances in sensation, hallucination, painful muscular contractions leading to epileptic convulsions, vomiting, and diarrhea, the diarrhea seems to be more prominent than described in the literature and is often bloody and no CNS (central nervous system) symptoms are described. Ergotism, however, bears consideration. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4104626,1780.]
